  "transcript": {
    "language": "en",
    "is_generated": true,
    "source": "whisper_local",
    "segments": [
      {
        "start": 0.0,
        "duration": 4.1,
        "text": "Let's design a program with objects and attributes."
      },
      {
        "start": 4.1,
        "duration": 2.4,
        "text": "We're building a site for our shoe store,"
      },
      {
        "start": 6.5,
        "duration": 3.5,
        "text": "where customers can browse through our product catalog."
      },
      {
        "start": 10.0,
        "duration": 2.4,
        "text": "Customers want to filter their search results"
      },
      {
        "start": 12.4,
        "duration": 2.7,
        "text": "based on the kind of shoes they're looking for."
      },
      {
        "start": 15.1,
        "duration": 2.9,
        "text": "So we need a program that can model the shoes"
      },
      {
        "start": 18.0,
        "duration": 4.4,
        "text": "in our catalog, and we need to search through those shoes"
      },
      {
        "start": 22.4,
        "duration": 3.2,
        "text": "to find the shoe that matches what the customer asked for."
      },
      {
        "start": 26.6,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "Our catalog has hundreds of pairs of shoes,"
      },
      {
        "start": 30.0,
        "duration": 3.6,
        "text": "but every pair has some things in common."
      },
      {
        "start": 33.6,
        "duration": 5.4,
        "text": "They all have a name, a color, a brand, and a size."
      },
      {
        "start": 41.4,
        "duration": 2.3,
        "text": "To represent a pair of shoes,"
      },
      {
        "start": 43.7,
        "duration": 2.3,
        "text": "the first thing we'll need is a class definition."
      },
      {
        "start": 47.0,
        "duration": 3.0,
        "text": "I'll let the IDE autocomplete this,"
      },
      {
        "start": 50.0,
        "duration": 2.8,
        "text": "and I'll name my data type, shoe."
      },
      {
        "start": 53.6,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "Now, we need to initialize our shoe attributes,"
      },
      {
        "start": 57.0,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "which we do in the init method."
      },
      {
        "start": 59.5,
        "duration": 2.9,
        "text": "So we'll pass in as parameters initial values"
      },
      {
        "start": 62.4,
        "duration": 3.1,
        "text": "for name, color, brand, and size."
      },
      {
        "start": 65.6,
        "duration": 3.6,
        "text": "And then we store those values on the object,"
      },
      {
        "start": 69.2,
        "duration": 4.1,
        "text": "setting up our attributes so we can access those values later."
      },
      {
        "start": 73.2,
        "duration": 2.4,
        "text": "We know Python passes in the object"
      },
      {
        "start": 75.7,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "through that first parameter, self."
      },
      {
        "start": 78.2,
        "duration": 5.0,
        "text": "So our init assignments always look like cell.attribute name."
      },
      {
        "start": 85.2,
        "duration": 2.8,
        "text": "Let's test that by creating a shoe object."
      },
      {
        "start": 88.0,
        "duration": 2.9,
        "text": "We know from our init method that we need to pass"
      },
      {
        "start": 90.9,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "in four arguments when we create a shoe,"
      },
      {
        "start": 93.6,
        "duration": 3.1,
        "text": "since we skip that first self parameter."
      },
      {
        "start": 96.7,
        "duration": 4.4,
        "text": "So let's say we have some air Jordans in black and red,"
      },
      {
        "start": 101.0,
        "duration": 2.7,
        "text": "made by Nike in a size eight."
      },
      {
        "start": 104.6,
        "duration": 3.0,
        "text": "And let's just check that data is getting stored."
      },
      {
        "start": 107.6,
        "duration": 3.1,
        "text": "By accessing our attributes after the object's created."
      },
      {
        "start": 111.8,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "Next, no bugs in our class definition."
      },
      {
        "start": 114.0,
        "duration": 2.8,
        "text": "So let's fill out the rest of our catalog."
      },
      {
        "start": 116.9,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "To do the search, we're going to need to iterate"
      },
      {
        "start": 120.2,
        "duration": 3.5,
        "text": "over every shoe to check if it matches."
      },
      {
        "start": 123.7,
        "duration": 3.0,
        "text": "So let's store our shoe objects in a list."
      },
      {
